# Next.js App Router Guide

This project uses Next.js 13+ with the App Router pattern. Here's how it works:

## App Router Structure
The `src/app` directory uses Next.js 13+ file-system based routing:

- `page.tsx` - Defines the UI for a route segment
- `layout.tsx` - Shared UI for a segment and its children
- `globals.css` - Global styles and Tailwind CSS imports

## Key Concepts

### Layouts
- [src/app/layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/layout.tsx) is the root layout
- Layouts wrap pages and other layouts
- They persist across route changes
- They can be nested

### Pages
- [src/app/page.tsx](mdc:src/app/page.tsx) is the main page
- Pages are UI components that are unique to a route
- They can fetch data and define metadata

### Styling
- [src/app/globals.css](mdc:src/app/globals.css) contains global styles
- Uses Tailwind CSS for utility-first styling
- PostCSS processes the styles (configured in [postcss.config.mjs](mdc:postcss.config.mjs))

## Development
- Run `npm run dev` to start the development server
- The app will be available at `http://localhost:3000`
- Changes to files in `src/app` will trigger hot reloading

